{"type":"message","id":"20e36a32","parentId":"652dd5e2","timestamp":"2026-02-18T19:32:57.849Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning job scraping framework**\n\nI'm considering how to create a structured plan for scraping job listings in Europe. The user wants to search and compile data into Excel, focusing on portfolio management and front office roles. I should propose a clear workflow, including milestones and legal considerations for scraping.\n\nIn terms of tools, we might use requests along with BeautifulSoup for static pages or Selenium for dynamic content. Once we gather data, we can store it in a CSV or Excel file using pandas and apply filters.\n\nWould the user like me to set up an automated scraping process? If so, I could implement a cron job or script.**Outlining scraping framework**\n\nI should propose a detailed scraping framework to target job listings in Europe. We need to respect guidelines such as using a user-agent and robots.txt while recognizing potential anti-scraping measures from sites like EFinancialCareers. \n\nFirst, let's define our scope to specific countries and establish data fields like job ID, title, company, and location. The steps include crawling with vector search, iterating results, normalizing locations, and writing to CSV before loading into Excel. \n\nFor output, I’ll create Excel sheets for raw data and filtered results. I could implement this in Python or Node.js, providing a structured repository with commands. Shall I proceed?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Nice goal. Here’s a concrete task/framework you can implement to crawl that page, gather Europe-wide jobs, and extract portfolio management/front-office roles into Excel.\n\nHigh-level plan\n- Define scope\n  - Region: Europe (explicitly include UK if desired; adjust by country list)\n  - Time filter: capture all jobs returned by the initial Europe search (no date filter unless you want to paginate)\n- Data model (per job)\n  - job_id, title, company, location, country, city (if available)\n  - location_raw, posted_time or posted_delta\n  - job_type (permanent/contract), seniority, function/sector\n  - url, source_page\n  - summary/snippet, requirements (if scraped)\n- Crawling strategy\n  - Start URL: https://www.efinancialcareers.com/jobs?enableVectorSearch=true\n  - Handle pagination if present (page tokens or “Next” links)\n  - Use a robust user-agent; respect robots.txt and site terms\n  - Extract structured fields from each listing card (title, company, location, date, link)\n  - Normalize location to country and city when possible\n- Data consolidation\n  - Write raw data to a CSV/JSON as you go\n  - Merge into a single Excel workbook with:\n    - Sheet1: Raw_Jobs\n    - Sheet2: Portfolio_and_FrontOffice (filtered subset)\n- Filtering & discovery\n  - Keywords for Portfolio/Front Office: portfolio, portfolio manager, PM, portfolio management, asset management, investment, trading, sales/trading, front office, researcher (if relevant), CIO/MD (senior front-office)\n  - Create two filtered views:\n    - PM_Roles: titles/descriptions matching portfolio management-related terms\n    - FrontOffice_Roles: broader front-office terms (trading, sales, structuring, research with a front-office tilt)\n- Output\n  - Excel workbook with two sheets (Raw_Jobs, Filtered_PM_and_FrontOffice)\n  - Optional: separate CSV exports for both filters\n- Reproducibility\n  - Provide a small script (Python or Node) with dependencies and a run command\n  - Include a README with setup, run, and tweak instructions\n\nRecommended implementation (concrete steps)\n- Language: Python (simple for data wrangling; good ecosystem for web scraping)\n- Libraries: requests or httpx, BeautifulSoup or lxml, pandas, openpyxl or xlsxwriter\n- Basic outline (pseudocode)\n  - import requests, bs4, pandas as pd\n  - base_url = \"https://www.efinancialcareers.com/jobs?enableVectorSearch=true\"\n  - for page in pages:\n      - html = fetch(page_url)\n      - parse listings: for card in html.select(listing_selector):\n          - extract: title, company, location, posted_time, url\n          - determine country/city from location (string parse; map known European countries)\n          - append dict to list\n  - df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n  - df.to_csv(\"raw_jobs.csv\", index=False)\n  - # Filtering\n  - pm_keywords = [\"portfolio\", \"portfolio manager\", \"PM\", \"portfolio management\", \"asset management\"]\n  - front_fx_keywords = [\"front office\", \"trading\", \"sales\", \"research\", \"invest\", \"quant\", \"quantitative\"]\n  - df_filtered = df[df[\"title\"].str.contains('|'.join(pm_keywords), case=False, na=False) |\n                  df[\"snippet\"].str.contains('|'.join(pm_keywords), case=False, na=False)]\n  - df_front = df[df[\"title\"].str.contains('|'.join(front_fx_keywords), case=False, na=False) |\n                   df[\"snippet\"].str.contains('|'.join(front_fx_keywords), case=False, na=False)]\n  - writer = pd.ExcelWriter(\"efinancial_jobs europe.xlsx\", engine=\"openpyxl\")\n  - df.to_excel(writer, sheet_name=\"Raw_Jobs\", index=False)\n  - df_filtered.to_excel(writer, sheet_name=\"Portfolio_and_FrontOffice\", index=False)\n  - df_front.to_excel(writer, sheet_name=\"FrontOffice_only\", index=False)\n  - writer.save()\n- Pagination and dynamic content\n  - If the site uses lazy loading, you might need Selenium or Playwright to render JS, then extract\n  - If API endpoints exist behind the vector search parameter, consider discovering the API calls and using them directly\n- Error handling\n  - Retry on transient network errors\n  - Skip listings missing essential fields; log a summary at end\n- Ethics & legality\n  - Respect terms of service and robots.txt\n  - Do not overwhelm the site with rapid requests; insert polite delays (e.g., 1–2 seconds between requests)\n  - Clearly store where data came from and how you’ll use it\n\nDeliverables you can ask me to generate for you\n- A ready-to-run Python script (requirements.txt included) that:\n  - Fetches the Europe-wide listings from the URL\n  - Parses listing cards, normalizes location, and saves a raw CSV\n  - Produces an Excel workbook with the Raw_Jobs and two filtered sheets (Portfolio_and_FrontOffice, FrontOffice_only)\n  - Logs a summary of counts and sample rows\n- A small README with setup and run instructions\n\nQuestions to tailor the plan\n- Should UK (London) be included as Europe or handled separately?\n- Do you want to also fetch job descriptions (full text) or only the summary from the listing?\n- Are you okay with a Python-based solution, or would you prefer Node.js?\n- Any preferred Excel layout (columns order, headers, or additional metadata like posted_time parsing)?\n\nIf you’d like, I can provide the first-pass Python script now and we can iterate based on any site quirks you encounter."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"auto","usage":{"input":9290,"output":2006,"cacheRead":2304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13600,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771443163795}}
