{"type":"message","id":"908dbc87","parentId":"1395b963","timestamp":"2026-02-18T19:33:40.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Providing template suggestions**\n\nI need to provide a concise template snippet for the user. I think it’s a good idea to suggest using Brave with the web_search tool since it doesn’t require a key. However, the user seems to want to use a key, so I'll ask for that and suggest storing it in an environment variable. Then, I can outline the next steps to help guide them through the process smoothly!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I don’t have a Brave API key yet in this session. If you want me to use Brave Search via the Brave API, please provide the key (and tell me where you want it stored securely, e.g., an environment variable or a secrets file).\n\nTypical integration (Brave API, assuming header-based key)\n- Endpoint: Brave Search API (e.g., https://api.brave.com/search or similar per current docs)\n- Auth header: X-Api-Key: YOUR_KEY (or Authorization: Bearer YOUR_KEY) depending on the docs\n- Example (Python requests):\n  - headers = {\"X-Api-Key\": \"<YOUR_KEY>\"}  # or \"Authorization\": \"Bearer <YOUR_KEY>\"\n  - resp = requests.get(\"https://api.brave.com/search\", headers=headers, params={\"q\": query, \"count\": 10})\n  - data = resp.json()\n\nWhat I can do next\n- If you provide the key (and preferred header name), I’ll wire Brave API calls into the scraping flow and replace or augment the web_fetch/web_search steps.\n- I can also store the key securely as an environment variable in this workspace (e.g., BRAVE_API_KEY) and reference it in the script, so you don’t have to paste it repeatedly.\n- If you’d rather, I can keep using the Brave-capable web_search tool without a key for public, low-volume queries, and switch to the Brave API only for deeper searches or larger runs when you supply the key.\n\nHow would you like to proceed?\n- Paste the Brave API key (and preferred header format), or\n- Tell me to proceed with a keyless Brave API path (using the existing web/search tool) and integrate the key later."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"auto","usage":{"input":6175,"output":1176,"cacheRead":6656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14007,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771443209673}}
